Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @sweet potato{1} into 1cm chunks (no need to peel).

Pop the diced sweet potato onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with oil, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer. TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until tender and golden, ~{15-20%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, cut the @medium tomato{1} into 1cm pieces.

Drain and rinse the @black beans{1} in a #sieve{}, then pop half of them into a #bowl{} and roughly mash with the back of a #fork{}.

Grate the @mature Cheddar cheese{80%g}.

Heat a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat (no oil). Once hot, add the @diced chorizo{90%g} and fry it until it starts to brown, ~{3-4%minutes}. Add a drizzle of oil to the frying pan and stir in the @tomato puree{30%g} and @Mexican style spice mix{1} and cook for ~{1%minute}.

Mix in the black beans (whole and mashed), @vegetable stock paste{10%g} and @water for the beans{150%ml}, then season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Simmer, stirring occasionally, until all the liquid has evaporated, ~{8-10%minutes}. Taste and season again if needed, then remove from the heat.

Once cooked, mix the roasted sweet potatoes into the bean mixture.

Lay the @plain taco tortillas{6} onto a lightly oiled baking tray and spoon the bean mixture onto one half of each one. Top with the grated cheese. Fold the other side over to make a semi-circle. Press down to keep together.

Rub a little oil over the top of each one, then bake on the top shelf of your oven until golden, ~{8-12%minutes}.

While the quesadillas bake, add the tomatoes and @olive oil for the dressing{1} to a medium bowl.

Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then mix well to combine.

Just before serving, add the @wild rocket{40%g} to the dressing and toss well to coat.

Once the quesadillas are cooked, transfer to your plates. Cut in half before serving if you'd like.

Serve with a dollop of @soured cream{75%g} on top and the salad alongside.

Enjoy!